      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/vr/force-at-40mm-noncannulated",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Force at 40 mm displacement QoI comparison — non-cannulated",
      "description": "This result represents the primary regulatory quantity of interest under ASTM F1717: the axial compressive force sustained at 40 mm crosshead displacement. The FEA ensemble (three independent analyst teams using FDA-supplied Ansys v19.2 models, DePuy Synthes internal Abaqus 2021 models, and an independent COMSOL 5.6 replication) predicted a mean force of 428.6 N (95% CI: 411.2–446.0 N) at 40 mm displacement. Experimental testing conducted at two ISO 17025-accredited biomechanics laboratories yielded a pooled mean of 421.3 N (SD 18.7 N, N=11 constructs: 6 at Lab A, 5 at Lab B). The percentage difference between ensemble mean prediction and experimental mean is 1.7%, satisfying the pre-specified <10% acceptance criterion. The validation uncertainty metric E/uval = 0.67, below the 1.96 threshold, confirming that the model-experiment discrepancy is within combined experimental and simulation uncertainty bounds. Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) material properties were sourced from ASTM F136-13 coupon testing conducted on the same material lot as the screw hardware. Contact interactions between screw shanks and UHMWPE vertebral body surrogates were modelled with a Coulomb friction coefficient of 0.25, calibrated from independent tribology measurements. Mesh convergence was demonstrated to within 1.3% for this QoI using a Richardson extrapolation study on three mesh densities (coarse 0.8 mm, medium 0.5 mm, fine 0.3 mm element edge length in the critical screw-rod interface region). All three analyst teams independently confirmed the 40 mm force prediction within a 3.1% inter-analyst spread, providing strong corroborating evidence of model robustness. The detailed simulation protocol, input deck version control records, and analyst sign-off sheets are archived in the sponsor's validated document management system (DMS ref: SIM-2023-NC-F1717-40MM-v3.1).",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/fea-ensemble-predictions-noncannulated"
    }
